---
// src/pages/disclaimer.astro
import PageLayout from "@/layouts/Base.astro";

const meta = {
	description:
		"Licensing framework, liability disclaimers, and bot policies for Decoding Invisible Systems.",
	title: "Licensing & Disclaimer",
};
---

<PageLayout meta={meta}>
	<div class="text-textColor space-y-6">
		<h1 class="title mb-6 text-2xl font-bold sm:text-3xl">Licensing & Disclaimer</h1>
		<p class="text-zinc-400">Last updated: June 2026</p>

		<hr class="border-zinc-700" />

		<section class="space-y-3">
			<h2 class="text-accent text-xl font-semibold">1. Copyright</h2>
			<p>
				Everything I write on this site—including essays, structural logs, map data, and code
				samples—belongs to me unless I specify otherwise.
			</p>
			<p class="rounded border border-zinc-700 bg-zinc-800/50 p-3 font-mono text-xs">
				Copyright &copy; 2026 Pranav A Elayidam. All Rights Reserved.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="space-y-3">
			<h2 class="text-accent text-xl font-semibold">2. Sharing Content (CC BY 4.0)</h2>
			<p>
				I believe in open data. All my original writing and research files are licensed under the
				<a
					href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/"
					class="text-accent hover:text-textColor underline"
					target="_blank"
					rel="noopener noreferrer"
				>
					Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0)
				</a> engine.
			</p>
			<p><strong>This means you are free to:</strong></p>
			<ul class="list-inside list-disc space-y-1 ps-2">
				<li>Copy, share, redistribute, and mirror this material anywhere you want.</li>
				<li>Remix, translate, or build on top of the content, even for commercial projects.</li>
			</ul>
			<p><strong>The only condition:</strong></p>
			<p>
				You must give clear credit by naming me (Pranav A Elayidam) and providing a direct link back
				to the original post on <em>Decoding Invisible Systems</em>.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="space-y-3">
			<h2 class="text-accent text-xl font-semibold">3. Technical Liability Shield</h2>
			<p>
				The data maps, network configurations, and computing breakdowns on this blog are shared
				strictly for educational and research purposes.
			</p>
			<p>
				I don't offer warranties or guarantees that these models are perfectly accurate or stable
				over time. If you copy an architecture setup, look at an infrastructure map, or test a code
				pattern, you do so completely at your own risk.
			</p>
			<p class="text-textColor font-semibold">
				I am not responsible if you break a real-world system, cause data loss, crash hardware, or
				misinterpret behavioral data models.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="space-y-3">
			<h2 class="text-accent text-xl font-semibold">4. Open-Source Template Attribution</h2>
			<p>
				The code engine, design layout, and Tailwind CSS rules for this website are built on top of
				the open-source
				<a
					href="https://github.com/chrismwilliams/astro-theme-cactus"
					class="text-accent hover:text-textColor underline"
					target="_blank"
					rel="noopener noreferrer"
				>
					astro-theme-cactus
				</a> template.
			</p>
			<p>
				The boilerplate software remains attributed to the creator. You can review his development
				profile directly at his GitHub handle:
				<a
					href="https://github.com/chrismwilliams"
					class="text-accent hover:text-textColor underline"
					target="_blank"
					rel="noopener noreferrer"
				>
					@chrismwilliams
				</a>.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="space-y-3 border-t border-zinc-800 pt-6">
			<h2 class="text-accent text-xl font-semibold">5. Automated Scraper & AI Bot Policy</h2>
			<p>
				If you are a web crawler, automated script, scraping engine, or an AI bot harvesting data:
				<strong>Do not scrape this site to train commercial models without explicit consent.</strong
				>
			</p>
			<p>
				Automated parsing of the markdown files inside my content directories for the purpose of
				ingestion into LLM training sets, commercial data brokers, or uncredited mirrors is a direct
				violation of this site's terms. Respect the <code>robots.txt</code> file rules.
			</p>
		</section>
	</div>
</PageLayout>
